  Description: 'With the most updated and state of the art training facilities, the
    Michigan Champions pride themselves on staying ahead of all the other teams.
    Always looking for an edge over the competition, this organization will not settle
    for second best. Despite not bringing home a championship the last few seasons,
    they still feel well accomplished with their trophy case  full of awards from
    the past. They keep their players motivated by showing off previous achievements
    and inspiring them to become the next winning squad that forever leaves their
    mark in the history books. Their motto: Do whatever it takes to get the win by
    adapting to their opponents and exploiting any weaknesses they find.'
  CoachName: Mitch North
